#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
grits-agent-secure  v0.3.0

Hardens your OpenClaw config. Before touching anything it:
  1. Shows you exactly what will change
  2. Creates a full backup with rollback instructions
  3. Asks for your confirmation
  4. Only then applies changes

Usage:
  ./grits-agent-secure               # preview mode (nothing changed)
  ./grits-agent-secure --apply       # apply fixes after confirmation
  ./grits-agent-secure --config /p   # custom config path
  ./grits-agent-secure --yes         # skip confirmation prompt (CI/scripts)

Auto-fixes:
  OC01  Enable host firewall (macOS Application Firewall / Linux UFW)
  OC07  Add dangerous tools to deny list
  OC09  Enable sandbox mode in agent config
  OC12  Fix .env file permissions (600, root-owned)
  OC13  Fix credentials directory permissions (700, root-owned)
  OC16  Disable dangerous runtime flags

Does NOT touch:
  - Existing firewall rules (additive only)
  - Tools you already allow (deny list is appended, not replaced)
  - Any other agent settings
  - File contents (permissions only)

Scored with GRITS v0.3.0 by X Scale AI
https://github.com/X-Scale-AI/grits-agent-scanner
"""

